Given that the GB/SA solvation treatment described here requires adding only two new parameters ( u in eq 2 and the dielectric offset used to compute 01 in eq 5) to those in an existing
force field, the correlation between our results and experiments or molecular solvent calculations is remarkable. Using analytical derivatives of eqs 2 and 5, we are able to carry out converged molecular mechanics or dynamics with only 2-4-fold reduction in speed over corresponding in vacuo calculations. In comparison with a single FEP calculation of AGd which requires several weeks of MicroVAX 3200 computer time, all 49 of the GB/SA calculations reported here were carried out within a total of 1 cpu min. The solvation treatment described should provide a major advance

